    $( For any neighborhood ` N ` of ` S ` , there is a neighborhood ` x ` of
       ` S ` such that ` N ` is a neighborhood of all subsets of ` x ` .  Based
       on Bourbaki TG I.3 Viv.  (Contributed by FL, 2-Oct-2006.) $)
    neissex $p |- ( ( J e. Top /\ N e. ( ( nei ` J ) ` S ) ) ->
   E. x e. ( ( nei ` J ) ` S ) A. y ( y C_ x -> N e. ( ( nei ` J ) ` y ) ) ) $=
